article.description: Thornton has career-best 22, UC Riverside beats Hawaii 66-62
article.headline: Thornton has career-best 22, UC Riverside beats Hawaii 66-62
article.linkText: Thornton has career-best 22, UC Riverside beats Hawaii 66-62
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- Steven Thornton scored a career-high 22 points, Jaylen Bland made the go-ahead 3-pointer and UC Riverside beat Hawaii 66-62 Saturday night. Bland finished with 15 points, including 3 of 4 free throws in the final 22 seconds to close out the win. Thornton hit a pair of free throws with 29.5 seconds left to give the Highlanders (9-9, 2-2 Big West) a 63-60 lead and Roderick Bobbitt answered with two free throws for Hawaii with 22.6 seconds left. Hawaii (13-6, 1-2) tied it at 58 on Stefan Jankovic's jumper, and Bland answered with a step-back 3 to put the Highlanders ahead for good 61-58 with 1:38 left. Jankovic had a career-high 17 points and Bobbitt added 10 points, six rebounds, five assists and five steals. Hawaii led by 13 in the first half, 31-28 at the break and 56-54 with 3:58 left in the game.
